Privacy Policy for H.I.L VPN

Effective Date: 10/20/2023

Introduction

H.I.L VPN ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to safeguarding your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines our practices concerning the collection, use, and disclosure of personal information when you use our VPN application (the "Service"). Please read this Privacy Policy carefully to understand how we handle your data.

1. Information We Collect

1.1. Personal Information
We may collect the following personal information:
- Your email address and username for account creation and authentication.
- Payment information when you subscribe to our premium service.
- Information you provide when you contact us for support.

1.2. Usage Information
We collect non-personal information that includes:
- Your IP address and the IP address of the VPN server you connect to.
- Connection timestamps, duration, and data transfer.
- Aggregated data to monitor the performance and usage of our service.

2. How We Use Your Information

2.1. To Provide and Improve the Service
We use your information to:
- Establish and manage your account.
- Process payments for premium subscriptions.
- Optimize and improve our service's performance and user experience.

2.2. Customer Support
We may use your information to respond to your requests and provide customer support.

2.3. Legal and Security Compliance
We may disclose your information if required by law or for security purposes.

3. Data Retention

We will retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required by law.

4. Data Security

We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data against unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data.

5. Third-Party Services

Our service may include links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for their privacy practices. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of those third parties.

6. Children's Privacy

Our service is not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from minors.

7. Updates to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our data practices or legal requirements. The latest version of the Privacy Policy will be available on our website.

8. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy or your personal information, please contact us at rdevzph@gmail.com.

